Raptors, Hawks play for possible home court in postseason

The Toronto Raptors and Atlanta Hawks rank fourth and fifth, respectively, in the Eastern Conference standings, and home-court advantage for a possible playoff series could loom large.  It is the last time the Raptors and Hawks play this season -- they split their two earlier games in Toronto.  Toronto (38-26) hopes to move up in the standings despite the loss of standout guard Kyle Lowry to wrist surgery.
